714552f-a.text:
4 East 78th Street, south side, east of Fifth Avenue (right).
Adjacent to the brownstone enumerated in a clearance that forms
the "K1" to provide a frontage on the Avenue, between 77th and
78th Streets. The apartment house to arise here is the Kingston.
The former home of Mrs. Jacob H. Schiff stood here from about 1901. Occupying the corner locations are the 16 story No. 960 Fifth Avenue and the darker 15 story No. 969. The latter is of recent construction, the former dating from 1926 when the mansion of Senator Wm. A. Clark was razed. This structure was of contemporary construction to the Schiff home.
Januar 20, 1938
Bernice Abbott, photo

709147f-a.text:
968-5, 964, 963 and 960 Fifth Ave., east side, south from East 78th to 77th Streets, showing arominently the Jacob H. Schiff house, No. 968-5, adjoining the S.E. corner (empty lot,former No. 969). On the extreme right is a part of No. 960, the Clark mansion, located at the N.E. corner of 77th Street. This, and its neighbor No. 963 were demolished in 1926 and on their site erected a large apartment house. The Schiff house, together with the empty lot will form the site of an 18-story apartment building according to the N.Y. Sun September 29, 1937.
June 1925.
